  "prompt": "How much time is required for the entire selection process of IAS?",
  "response": "The entire IAS (Indian Administrative Service) selection process typically takes around 1-1.5 years and involves several stages:\n\n1. Preliminary Examination\n- Conducted once a year\n- Duration: 2 hours\n- Objective type multiple-choice questions\n- Screening test to qualify for Main Examination\n\n2. Main Examination\n- Conducted after clearing prelims\n- Held over 5-6 days\n- Includes written papers on various subjects\n- Requires comprehensive preparation\n\n3. Personality Test/Interview\n- Conducted after clearing Main Examination\n- Usually lasts 30-45 minutes\n- Assesses candidate's personality, communication skills, and overall suitability\n\n4. Final Selection\n- Based on combined scores of Main Examination and Interview\n- Ranking determined\n- Allocation of services\n\nTotal Timeline:\n- Preliminary Exam: Usually held in June\n- Main Examination: Typically in September-October\n- Interview: Conducted between February-March of the following year\n- Final result and training: By May-June\n\nFrom initial application to final selection, the entire process usually takes approximately 12-18 months, depending on UPSC's schedule and administrative procedures.",
